<p><b>Method</b></p>

<ul>
  <li>Sunflower Oil – 120ml/3/4 cup</li>
  <li>Soft Dark Brown Sugar – 200g/1 cup</li>
  <li>Golden Syrup – 2 tbsp</li>
  <li>Peanut Butter – 1 tbsp</li>
  <li>Vanilla Extract – 1/2 tsp</li>
</ul>

<p>Melt these ingredients in a pan over a low heat until melted and mixed together.</p>

<p>Next, add:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Sesame Seeds – 25g / 2 tbsp</li>
  <li>Sunflower Seeds – 25g / 2 tbsp</li>
  <li>Flaked Almonds – 50g / 1/2 cup</li>
  <li>Sultanas – 50g / 1/2 cup</li>
  <li>Chopped Dates – 50g / 1/2 cup</li>
</ul>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Gradually stir in thick cut porridge oats/oatmeal – 225g / 8 oz</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Transfer mixture to a baking tin lined with parchment – roughly 25 x 15cm or 10 x 6 inches. Press down firmly with a metal fork.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Place in an oven at 180degrees C, 350 degrees F or gas mark 4 for 10 to 15 minutes, keeping an eye on them so they don’t get over done.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Finally, leave to cool in the tin before you take them out and cut them</p>
  </li>
</ol>
